# Java JDK

Every programming language need a platform to run like c++ needs **MinGW**, python needs python runtime.Just like that Java needs JDK.
**JDK** or **Java Development Kit**-
  - provides environment to test and develop Java programs.
  - It has vast packages that includes :-
     1. **JRE** :- Runtime environment to execute program.
     2. **Compiler** :- Javac.
     3. **Docs Generator** :- Java Document.
     4. **Loader/Interpreter**.
     5. **Development tools** :- Provides runtime for particular java program.

---

# Installation

## Linux

1. Open the terminal (**Ctrl**+**Alt**+**T**) and update your package repository.

`sudo apt update`

2. Run the following command to install latest **Java Development Kit**

`sudo apt install default-jdk`

3. Type **y** to confirm and hit **Enter**

![Image](https://phoenixnap.com/kb/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/install-default-jdk-ubuntu.png)

---

## Windows

1. Head to this [link](https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase-downloads.html) and download JDK.

![Image](https://phoenixnap.com/kb/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/install-default-jdk-ubuntu.png)

2. Accept the license agreement and download JDK as per your system architecture(32bit or 64 bit)

![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/2/javainstall-2.png)

3. You will need to create Oracle account to download Java 8, so follow the steps and you are good to go

4. Run the JDK installer once the download is complete

![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/2/javainstall-4.png)

5. Follow the steps by clicking next... Leave everything default
 
 ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/2/javainstall-6.png)

 ### Here is the crucial step, you have to set the environment path variable in order for java to run on Windows.

 The path variable gives location of Java executable, and the full path is C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_271\bin . Copy this as per your directory.

 1. Right click on my computer. **Select Properties**

  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/java/111417_1107_Java25.png)

2. Click **Advanced System Settings**
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/2/java-install-20.png)

3. Click on **Environment Variables**
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/java/111417_1107_Java27.png)

4. Click on **New** button
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/java/1912211_install_javaimage9.jpg)

5. In Variable name TYPE **PATH**
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/java/111417_1107_Java29.png)

6. Copy the path of bin folder mentioned above
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/2/java-install-21.png)

7. Paste path in **Variable Value** and Hit OK
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/2/java-install-22.png)

8. Open powershell or command prompt type `javac` to check if jdk is installed or not.
  ![Image](https://cdn.guru99.com/images/java/1912211_install_javaimage15.jpg)


## Mac OS

1. Download .dmg file for mac Installation
  ![Image](https://i2.wp.com/techdecodetutorials.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2_20210708_152537_0001.png?resize=1024%2C576&ssl=1)

2. Agree with the license agreement
  ![Image](https://i0.wp.com/techdecodetutorials.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/3_20210708_152537_0002.png?resize=1024%2C576&ssl=1)

3. Open DMG file and a welcome windows for Installation will appear
  ![Image](https://i0.wp.com/techdecodetutorials.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/6_20210708_152537_0005.png?resize=1024%2C576&ssl=1)

4. In the installation window click on the install button, if asked enter the password of your Mac machine and JDK installation will begin.

5. Verify install by opening terminal and typing `java --version` command to see if installation is properly done or not
